						               													<description>The card game &amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#153;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#166;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#140;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#135;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#168;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#154;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#164;&amp;#229;&amp;#132;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#151;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#132;&amp;#228;&amp;#184;&amp;#150;&amp;#231;&amp;#149;&amp;#140; (A World Where Everything Is a Little Kinder) is a press-your-luck set-collection game based upon the manga of the same title.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game, players aim to either fulfill the victory condition of a specific card they have been dealt or collect one of each type of item cards. The deck consists of 46 item cards, which come in seven types, and 4 light tree cards. On a turn, you reveal cards from the top of the deck, one at a time. With each reveal, you can choose to stop and collect the cards revealed &amp;mdash; but if the last revealed card matches one of the previously revealed cards, all of the revealed cards are discarded, and play moves to the next player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
